clauseList.text: Mortgage insurer's undertaking to insure, subject to any further conditions as stipulated by mortgage insurer.  Mortgagee accepts that all fees and premiums charged by mortgage insurer are the borrower's responsibility and will be deducted from the first advance or as agreed to. (Applicant)
The Lender reserves the right to cancel or amend the Commitment if the Property is not being occupied as the Borrower's principal residence. (Applicant)

The Borrower(s) is responsible for the payment of property taxes.  The payment of property taxes will be made through a pre-authorized payment plan offered by the Municipality.  The Borrower will provide confirmation to MCM QA - Macquarie that the property has been enrolled in such plan. In addition, the Borrower is responsible for claiming any Home Owner's Grants or tax subsidies available from the municipal tax offices.   Further, confirmation that property taxes have been paid and are update, and, if applicable, any changes to available grants or subsidies,  is required to be sent to MCM QA - Macquarie within 30 days from the date for final payment in each calendar year. (Applicant)

The Borrower(s) is entitled to prepay the entire amount owned under this Mortgage before the Maturity Date subject to a prepayment penalty.  The prepayment penalty will be the greater of (A) three months' interest and (B) the interest rate differential, that being, the difference between the interest rate of the mortgage and the current prevailing interest rate offered by the Mortgagee for a term comparable to the remaining term of this mortgage, calculated on the outstanding balance. (Applicant)
In the case of an open mortgage, the Borrower(s), provided the loan is not in default, is entitled to fully or partially repay the mortgage balance outstanding without penalty. (Applicant)

Prior to releasing any mortgage proceeds, the solicitor will carry out the necessary searches with respect to any liens, encumbrances, executions; that may be registered against the property. (Applicant)
No deletions from or additions to the Mortgage are permissible unless approved by MCM QA - Macquarie. (Applicant)
The Mortgage is to be prepared in the name of MCM QA - Macquarie (Applicant)
The 'Mortgage Requirements' section in the Solicitor's Guide contains information required to prepare the mortgage. (Applicant)

If, at any time or from time to time, any default or breach of covenant occurs under any encumbrances registered against the land and which encumbrance has priority over this Mortgage, it shall constitute default under this Mortgage and we may pay all monies and take appropriate action to cure any default or breach under any such encumbrance.  All costs, fees, charges, expenses and amounts paid by MCM QA - Macquarie to cure any default or breach under any such prior encumbrance, shall be charged on the land and secured under this Mortgage and shall be recoverable by us in the same manner as any default or breach of covenant under this Mortgage. (Applicant)

MCM QA - Macquarie reserves the right, should the property taxes fall into arrears, to take over the payment of property taxes and bill the mortgagor(s) with their regular principal and interest payments. Any fees and penalties incurred as a result of the property tax arrears will the sole responsibility of the Borrower(s). (Applicant)

This mortgage will be subject to all extended terms set forth in the MCM QA - Macquarie's standard form of mortgage contract or in the mortgage contract prepared by our solicitors whichever the case may be. (Applicant)

Title to the property must be acceptable to our Solicitor who will ensure that the Mortgagor(s) have good and marketable title in fee simple to the property and that it is clear of any encumbrances which might affect the priority of this Mortgage.  Alternatively, MCM QA - Macquarie will accept Title Insurance from a Title Insurance provider acceptable to the Lender. (Applicant)
There may be a fee charged for any payment that is returned or dishonoured. (Applicant)
MCM QA - Macquarie reserves the right to request the Borrower(s) to retain a solicitor that is on the Lender's approved list, at the Borrower(s) expense. (Applicant)
This Commitment shall be open for acceptance by you until 11:59 pm on  after which time, if not accepted, shall be considered null and void. (Applicant)
The terms in this commitment cannot be altered unless confirmed in writing by MCM QA - Macquarie. (Applicant)

Please provide a void cheque with the acceptance of this commitment showing your complete banking information.  By signing this document, you hereby authorize the servicing company, to debit the following account for mortgage payments as noted herein. (Applicant)

MCM QA - Macquarie reserves the right to approve all subsequent purchasers prior to mortgage assumption or transfer, otherwise, upon vacating or selling the mortgaged property, this loan becomes due and payable. (Applicant)

In the case of porting, the Borrower(s) may transfer the remaining mortgage balance together with the interest rate set out herein to the new property provided that the Mortgage Loan is not in default; a new mortgage loan application has been accepted by the MCM QA - Macquarie; all terms and conditions set out in the subsequent Mortgage Loan approval have been met and the closing dates of the two properties are within 30 days.   In the event that the existing mortgage is fully or partially repaid and the new mortgage is not proceeded with, a prepayment penalty will apply.  In the event that the new mortgage amount is less than the existing mortgage amount, the difference between the two amounts will be deemed to be a partial repayment and will be subject to a penalty. (Applicant)

The applicant is responsible for any costs relating to the mortgage including legal, appraisal, survey, Title Insurance or inspection fees, unless otherwise specified in this commitment letter. (Applicant)
Notwithstanding the registration of the mortgage and advances made pursuant to same, the terms and conditions of this commitment shall remain binding and effective on the parties hereto. (Applicant)
The Borrower(s) will be responsible for the cost of each inspection.  Inspections are for the sole benefit of MCM QA - Macquarie and not for supervision on your behalf. (Applicant)

MCM QA - Macquarie does not arrange for the mortgage to have the benefit of life, critical illness, job loss or disability insurance.  If this coverage is desired, the Borrower(s) must arrange for these services, solely at their expense. (Applicant)
This mortgage is subject to a Lending Fee of $0.00. This amount will be deducted from the total loan amount shown above. (Applicant)

MCM QA - Macquarie reserves the right to amend or cancel this application if the documentation received is not satisfactory and/or if it differs from the information shown on the application. (Applicant)

MCM QA - Macquarie has the sole discretion to renew this mortgage at maturity for any term, with or without change in the interest rate payable under the Mortgage, by entering into one or more written agreements with the mortgagor(s). (Applicant)

When the mortgage loan is not in default, the Borrower(s) are entitled to make privilege payments, and to increase their principal and interest payment.  The amount of the privilege payment and principal and interest payment increase should be confirmed with the Lender prior to closing. (Applicant)
ERRORS AND OMISSIONS EXCEPTED (Applicant)

A Financing Disclosure Statement will be required to be signed in accordance with the Consumer Protection Legislation of your province.   In addition, certification will be required that all requirements under the Matrimonial Property Act in your province have been met and that the status does not in any way affect MCM QA - Macquarie's charge.  All copies of the Disclosure Statements must be original signature.  These documents will be executed by your Solicitor. (Solicitor)
MCM QA - Macquarie requires that Fire Insurance, acceptable to the Lender, with loss payable to MCM QA - Macquarie  must be arranged prior to any advance of funds. (Solicitor)

Prior to the submitting for Title Insurance in this registration of this mortgage, MCM QA - Macquarie requires the following: confirmation that property taxes are up-to-date, a copy of the fire insurance policy, a copy of the deed or title to the property in order to obtain legal description and registration numbers and that the enclosed 'Authorization to use Title Insurance' is signed and returned to us.  All fees are the responsibility of the Borrower(s).  If the copy of the deed or title is not available or if remote signing of the documents is required, there may be additional search fees applicable. (Solicitor)

Where the Date of Advance of funds for this Mortgage is prior to the Interest Adjustment Date, an Interest Adjustment Payment will be required.  The Payment is to be made by post-dated cheque, to be dated on the Interest Adjustment Date, for the amount as set out in the Statement of Disclosure, and provided to the solicitor prior to the advance of funds under this Mortgage. (Solicitor)

We require receipt of a satisfactory written report confirming any existing mortgage has been paid as agreed and is up to date, outlining all amounts outstanding and monthly payments and that existing mortgage balance and related monthly payments do not exceed the amounts declared in the application. (Solicitor)
A statutory declaration indicating that the property will be occupied by the applicant(s) as their principal residence. (Solicitor)
MCM QA - Macquarie refuse any subsequent financial charges to be registered against the subject property without our approval. (Solicitor)

MCM QA - Macquarie must receive a copies of the fully executed Agreement of Purchase and Sale and MLS Listing for the property being purchased.  Such documents must be deemed acceptable to MCM QA - Macquarie. (Broker)
Signed Commitment (Broker)
MCM QA - Macquarie will require a Surveyor's Certificate or Title Insurance, acceptable to the Lender, at the cost of the Borrower(s). (Broker)
MCM QA - Macquarie requires written confirmation of the source of down payment from non-borrowed cash equity.  Such confirmation must be acceptable to the Lender. (Broker)
We require verification of Rental Income, by way of a signed lease agreement between landlord and tenant. (Broker)

MCM QA - Macquarie will require copies of personal tax returns and assessment notices for the last 3 years confirming a mininum net income as declared on the Borrower(s) credit application as well 3 years financial statements for the business for FIVEOH TestHawaii. (Broker)

MCM QA - Macquarie requires receipt of a letter from FIVEOH2 FIVEOH's employer(s) confirming the following:  a full or part-time position that is not probationary; income and length of employment as declared on the credit application.  In addition, MCM QA - Macquarie also requires a year to day pay slip and a copy of a Revenue Canada Notice of Assessment for the previous year or a copy of the Borrower(s) T4.  Information received must be satisfactory to MCM QA - Macquarie and will be verified prior to funding this mortgage.  A 2 year average will be used in qualifying the income. (Broker)
